# 🔐 .env Configuration Template

Copy this file to `backend/.env` and fill in your credentials.

```bash
# ============================================================================
# 🚨 IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
# 1. This file contains sensitive credentials - NEVER commit to Git
# 2. Add .env to .gitignore (it should already be there)
# 3. Never share credentials with anyone
# 4. Delete and recreate keys if they're exposed
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# MongoDB connection (if using MongoDB instead of DynamoDB)
# MONGODB_URL=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/
DB_NAME=stressdetect

# DynamoDB region (AWS)
DYNAMODB_REGION=us-east-1

# ============================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION
# ============================================================================

# Generate strong JWT secret:
# Option 1: Use Python: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
# Option 2: Use OpenSSL: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET_KEY=your_generated_secret_key_here_min_32_chars
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_EXPIRATION_HOURS=24

# ============================================================================
# AWS CREDENTIALS (For ALL AWS Services)
# ============================================================================

# Get from: AWS Console → IAM → Users → Your User → Security Credentials
# Format: AKIA + 16 characters
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY

# S3 Bucket name (create this first in AWS Console)
# Must be globally unique
AWS_S3_BUCKET=stressdetect-exports-YOUR_NAME

# SNS Topic ARN (create this in AWS Console)
# Format: arn:aws:sns:region:account_id:topic_name
AWS_SNS_TOPIC_ARN=arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:123456789012:stressdetect-alerts

# Email to send FROM (must be verified in SES)
# For development: your email + verified in AWS SES
AWS_SES_SENDER=noreply@stressdetect.app
AWS_SES_SENDER_NAME=Stress Detect

# ============================================================================
# AZURE CREDENTIALS - TEXT ANALYTICS
# ============================================================================

# Get from: Azure Portal → Text Analytics Resource → Keys and Endpoint
# Key: 32 character hex string
# Endpoint: https://region.api.cognitive.microsoft.com/
AZURE_TEXT_ANALYTICS_KEY=0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef
AZURE_TEXT_ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT=https://eastus.api.cognitive.microsoft.com/

# ============================================================================
# AZURE CREDENTIALS - SIGNALR
# ============================================================================

# Get from: Azure Portal → SignalR Service → Keys
# Format: Endpoint=https://...;AccessKey=...;Version=1.0;
AZURE_SIGNALR_CONNECTION_STRING=Endpoint=https://stressdetect-signalr.service.signalr.net/;AccessKey=0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef=;Version=1.0;

# ============================================================================
# LOGGING CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# Log level: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Log file location (relative to backend directory)
LOG_FILE=app.log

# CloudWatch log group name (AWS)
AWS_CLOUDWATCH_LOG_GROUP=/stressdetect/api

# ============================================================================
# FEATURE FLAGS
# ============================================================================

# Enable/disable cloud services
ENABLE_EMAIL_ALERTS=true
ENABLE_CLOUD_BACKUP=true
ENABLE_REALTIME_UPDATES=true
ENABLE_NLP_ANALYSIS=true
ENABLE_MONITORING=true

# ============================================================================
# THRESHOLDS AND CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# Stress level threshold for alerts (0-100)
STRESS_ALERT_THRESHOLD=75

# Email alert threshold (0-100)
HIGH_STRESS_THRESHOLD=80

# Cache TTL in seconds
CACHE_TTL=3600

# API rate limit (requests per minute)
RATE_LIMIT=100

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL - THIRD PARTY INTEGRATIONS
# ============================================================================

# Email configuration (for direct SMTP if needed)
# EMAIL_BACKEND=smtp
# EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# EMAIL_PORT=587
# EMAIL_USERNAME=your_email@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password

# Slack notifications (optional)
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/YOUR/WEBHOOK/URL

# Sentry error tracking (optional)
# SENTRY_DSN=https://key@sentry.io/project_id

# ============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT
# ============================================================================

# API environment: development, staging, production
ENVIRONMENT=development

# API base URL
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Frontend URL
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# CORS allowed origins
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:3000","http://localhost:5173","https://stressdetect.app"]

# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT (Set these when deploying to production)
# ============================================================================

# Set to false when deploying
DEBUG=true

# Allow CORS in production
ALLOW_CORS=true

# Database connection timeout
DB_TIMEOUT=30

# Request timeout
REQUEST_TIMEOUT=30
```

---

## 📋 How to Fill This Out

### 1️⃣ **AWS Credentials** (2 minutes)

Goes here:
```
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=YOUR_ACCESS_KEY
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=YOUR_SECRET_KEY
```

Follow: `API_KEYS_CREDENTIALS_GUIDE.md` → AWS Credentials Setup section

### 2️⃣ **Azure Text Analytics** (2 minutes)

Goes here:
```
AZURE_TEXT_ANALYTICS_KEY=YOUR_KEY
AZURE_TEXT_ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT=YOUR_ENDPOINT
```

Follow: `API_KEYS_CREDENTIALS_GUIDE.md` → Azure Credentials Setup section

### 3️⃣ **Azure SignalR** (2 minutes)

Goes here:
```
AZURE_SIGNALR_CONNECTION_STRING=YOUR_CONNECTION_STRING
```

Follow: `API_KEYS_CREDENTIALS_GUIDE.md` → Azure Credentials Setup section

### 4️⃣ **Generate JWT Secret** (1 minute)

Run this in Python:
```python
import secrets
print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))
```

Output looks like: `abc123def456ghi789jkl012mno34pqr56stu78vwx90`

Goes here:
```
JWT_SECRET_KEY=abc123def456ghi789jkl012mno34pqr56stu78vwx90
```

### 5️⃣ **Create S3 Bucket** (1 minute)

In AWS Console or CLI:
```bash
aws s3 mb s3://stressdetect-exports-$(whoami)
```

Goes here:
```
AWS_S3_BUCKET=stressdetect-exports-yourname
```

### 6️⃣ **Create SNS Topic** (1 minute)

In AWS Console or CLI:
```bash
aws sns create-topic --name stressdetect-alerts
# Copy the ARN from output
```

Goes here:
```
AWS_SNS_TOPIC_ARN=arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID:stressdetect-alerts
```

