## ✅ Verification

After filling everything out:

```bash
# 1. Check file exists and is readable
cat backend/.env | head -20
# Should show your values

# 2. Test Python can load it
python -c "from dotenv import load_dotenv; import os; load_dotenv(); print(f'AWS: {os.getenv(\"AWS_REGION\")}')"
# Output: AWS: us-east-1

# 3. Test AWS CLI with your keys
aws s3 ls
# Should list S3 buckets without errors

# 4. Test Python imports
python -c "import boto3; import azure; print('All working!')"
# Output: All working!
```

