## 🆘 If Credentials Get Exposed

**IMMEDIATELY DO THIS:**

```bash
# 1. Delete compromised AWS key
aws iam delete-access-key --access-key-id AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE --user-name stressdetect-dev

# 2. Delete compromised Azure key
# Go to Azure Portal → Text Analytics → Keys → Regenerate

# 3. Create new keys
aws iam create-access-key --user-name stressdetect-dev
# OR in Azure Portal → Create new key

# 4. Update .env with new credentials
# Edit backend/.env

# 5. DO NOT commit the .env file itself
# Only commit that you changed it
git add -u  # Update tracked files only
git commit -m "Regenerated API keys (credentials rotated locally)"
```

